Executive Order 13587, issued by President Barack Obama in October 2011, focuses on improving the security of classified networks and the responsible sharing and safeguarding of classified information. The order recognizes the need for immediate sharing of classified information with authorized users around the world, while also emphasizing the importance of secure sharing. It directs structural reforms to ensure responsible sharing and safeguarding of classified information on computer networks. The order establishes the Senior Information Sharing and Safeguarding Steering Committee, responsible for developing and implementing policies and standards for sharing and safeguarding classified information. It also establishes the Classified Information Sharing and Safeguarding Office and the Insider Threat Task Force to provide expert support and develop programs for deterring, detecting, and mitigating insider threats. The order assigns various responsibilities to agencies and sets out general provisions to ensure compliance with established policies and standards, while also protecting privacy and civil liberties.